# Proposal Row Templates — Wave-1 AskUserQuestion Row Variants
#
# SCOPE is baked into the row variant tag — no separate scope question is emitted
# (R14, Iteration-2 collapse). Each row encodes: intent + scope + name + description
# + estimated size + complexity rating.
#
# SOFT CAP: 8 rows maximum in a single Wave-1 AskUserQuestion. When more candidates
# exist, collapse low-confidence ones into the overflow row (last variant below).
# For ambiguous-scope [NEW] candidates, emit only the more-likely scope when the
# total row count would otherwise exceed 8.
#
# OVERFLOW ROW: used when N additional low-confidence candidates were identified but
# omitted to stay within the soft cap. Replace {{N}} with the actual count.
#
# Row variants (each on its own line below — emit exactly one per proposal):

[NEW@global] {{NAME}} — {{DESCRIPTION}} (~{{LINES}} lines, {{COMPLEXITY}})
[NEW@local] {{NAME}} — {{DESCRIPTION}} (~{{LINES}} lines, {{COMPLEXITY}})
[UPDATE→{{EXISTING_NAME}}] {{NAME}} — {{DESCRIPTION}} (~{{LINES}} lines, {{COMPLEXITY}})
[+{{N}} more low-confidence candidates omitted]
